Bring a pan of water to the simmer and place a bamboo steamer on top.Arrange the lemon slices in the steamer and place the mackerel fillets inside. Season with salt and freshly ground black pepper.  Steam for 3-4 minutes, or until cooked.For the leeks, heat the red wine in a pan.  Add the leeks. Poach for 4-5 minutes, until tender.To serve, place the mackerel fillets on a serving plate and spoon the poached leeks alongside.